reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Portable and easy to use
reviews.reviewText: This projector is small and lightweight, easy to carry and set up wherever you go. We watch movies in the living room every weekend, and sometimes we also move to the bedroom to watch live TV. This projector also has an app store, making it convenient to install apps. The picture looks great with its native 1080p resolution.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good quality FHD portable projector with low price
reviews.reviewText: Pros: This FHD projector boasts a high-resolution display and comes equipped with smart apps, adding versatility to your viewing experience.Cons: The only drawback appears to be a slightly noisy fan, which might be noticeable during quieter moments.Overall, this projector offers excellent value for its price, delivering impressive FHD image quality. One potential improvement could be the inclusion of autofocus, enhancing user convenience.Regarding the smart apps, the reviewer has not had the opportunity to test them or explore the app store yet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not too bright
reviews.reviewText: This projector, while small and easily portable, does not put out a lot of lumens. It is best used in a very dark room and relatively close to the screen. It was easy to set up and runs well on its battery as well as when plugged in. I cannot comment on the sound quality as I HDMI'd it to my soundbar. I have also not yet used any of the built-in apps. Picture quality is just OK; it's better with animation than actual video, likely because of the clearer delineation present in animation as opposed to "real life" recordings. This is the first projector I've owned so I don't have a lot of ability to compare, but I suspect I might have been better off going for a higher-quality/less cheap model.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice little projector
reviews.reviewText: this little projector is really cute and it works great. it is battery powered, rechargeable. You can take it anywhere and it can connect to phone, pc, video game systems, all kinds of different ways to play whatever you want to watch on the projector. The picture is very clear, much better than i would have expected for the little machine. I would say it competes well with the larger projectors. I have used it on a white wall, on a brick wall, and even on the ceiling and had a great viewing experience every time. The speakers work really well, plenty loud for everyone in the room to hear. Battery lasts quite a while. You can watch a few movies or several episodes of a show on one charge. It recharges pretty fast also. The price is reasonable and the quality is good. I would recommend to others
